---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import SiteNav from '../../../components/SiteNav.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../../../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---
<Base
  lang="en"
  title="Privacy Policy | CreativeCinema GmbH"
  description="Privacy policy of CreativeCinema GmbH – information on the processing of personal data under the GDPR."
  path="privacy/"
  hasEN={false}
  robots="noindex, follow"
  noHreflang={true}
>
  <SiteNav lang="en" />

  <main class="legal" id="produktion">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="section-h">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Protecting your personal data is important to us. Below we inform you, in accordance with Articles&nbsp;13 and&nbsp;14
          of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), which data we process when you visit this website and for what
          purpose.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Controller</h2>
        <p>
          The controller responsible for data processing on this website is:<br />
          <strong>CreativeCinema GmbH</strong><br />
          Gundstraße 13a, 91056 Erlangen, Germany<br />
          Represented by: Andreas Schulz<br />
          Phone: <a href="tel:+491748484842">+49 174 8484842</a> · Email: <a href="mailto:info@creative-cinema.net">info@creative-cinema.net</a>
        </p>

        <h2>2. Data Protection Officer</h2>
        <p>Andreas Schulz · <a href="mailto:info@creative-cinema.net">info@creative-cinema.net</a></p>

        <h2>3. Hosting</h2>
        <p>
          This website is hosted by an external service provider (<strong>one.com</strong>, one.com Group AB). The personal
          data collected when you visit the website is processed on the host's servers within the European Union. A data
          processing agreement pursuant to Article&nbsp;28 GDPR is in place with the host. The legal basis is our legitimate
          interest in the secure and efficient provision of our website (Article&nbsp;6(1)(f) GDPR).
        </p>

        <h3>Server log files</h3>
        <p>
          When you access the website, information that your browser transmits is automatically collected and stored in
          so-called server log files. This includes: browser type and version, the operating system used, the referrer URL,
          the host name of the accessing device, the time of the server request and the IP address. This data is not merged
          with other data sources. Processing is based on Article&nbsp;6(1)(f) GDPR for the technically error-free presentation
          and security of our systems. The log files are stored only for as long as necessary for these purposes and then
          deleted.
        </p>

        <h2>4. SSL/TLS encryption</h2>
        <p>
          For security reasons, this site uses SSL/TLS encryption. You can recognise an encrypted connection by the
          “https://” in your browser's address bar. This means the data you transmit to us cannot be read by third parties.
        </p>

        <h2 id="cookies">5. Cookies &amp; consent</h2>
        <p>
          On this website we use exclusively <strong>technically necessary cookies</strong> or local storage that are required
          to operate the site (e.g. to store your cookie choice). No consent is required for this pursuant to Section&nbsp;25(2)
          TDDDG; the legal basis is Article&nbsp;6(1)(f) GDPR.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> currently use any tracking, analysis of your usage behaviour or marketing cookies. Should
          optional services (e.g. reach measurement) be used in the future, this will only happen after your explicit consent
          via our consent banner (Article&nbsp;6(1)(a) GDPR, Section&nbsp;25(1) TDDDG). Your consent is voluntary and can be
          withdrawn at any time with effect for the future.
        </p>
        <p>
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost" onclick="window.openCookieSettings && window.openCookieSettings()">Change cookie settings</button>
        </p>

        <h2>6. Fonts (self-hosted)</h2>
        <p>
          For a consistent appearance we use the fonts “Poppins” and “Source Sans&nbsp;3”. These are served
          <strong>locally from our own server</strong>. There is <strong>no connection to Google servers</strong> and
          <strong>no IP address is transmitted to third parties</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Contact form &amp; contact by email</h2>
        <p>
          If you contact us via the contact form or by email, we process the data you provide (e.g. name, email address,
          phone number where applicable, subject/preferred date and the content of your message) in order to handle your
          enquiry. Mandatory fields are marked as such; all other information is voluntary.
        </p>
        <p>
          The legal basis is Article&nbsp;6(1)(b) GDPR where your enquiry relates to the initiation or performance of a
          contract; otherwise Article&nbsp;6(1)(f) GDPR (our legitimate interest in answering enquiries) or Article&nbsp;6(1)(a)
          GDPR where you have given consent. The message is transmitted as an email to our mailbox
          <a href="mailto:info@creative-cinema.net">info@creative-cinema.net</a> (via the email service of our host one.com).
        </p>
        <p>
          To protect against automated misuse (spam) we use technical measures that work without external services and without
          tracking (a hidden honeypot field and a timing check on submission). No additional personal data is passed on to
          third parties in the process.
        </p>
        <p>
          We store your enquiry until it has been fully processed and there is no further reason to retain it. Statutory
          retention obligations (e.g. under commercial and tax law) remain unaffected.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
        <p>You have the following rights with regard to your personal data:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Right of access (Article&nbsp;15 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to rectification (Article&nbsp;16 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to erasure (Article&nbsp;17 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to restriction of processing (Article&nbsp;18 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to data portability (Article&nbsp;20 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to object to processing (Article&nbsp;21 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to withdraw consent with effect for the future (Article&nbsp;7(3) GDPR)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise your rights, an informal message to the contact details above is sufficient.</p>

        <h2>9. Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</h2>
        <p>
          Without prejudice to other remedies, you have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory
          authority. The authority responsible for us is the <strong>Bavarian State Office for Data Protection Supervision
          (BayLDA)</strong>, Promenade 18, 91522 Ansbach, Germany.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Objection to advertising emails</h2>
        <p>
          We hereby object to the use of contact data published within the scope of the legal-notice obligation for sending
          unsolicited advertising and information material. The operators of the site expressly reserve the right to take
          legal action in the event of the unsolicited sending of advertising information, e.g. through spam emails.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Currency of this policy</h2>
        <p>
          This privacy policy is currently valid. Due to the further development of our website or changes in legal or
          regulatory requirements, it may become necessary to amend this policy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="legal-back"><a href="/en/">← Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter lang="en" />
</Base>
